templateVersions.content:
You are an expert escalation risk analyst for a telecom service desk. Your task is to assess the escalation risk for the support case below and return a structured JSON response ONLY - no explanations, no prose, no markdown.

## Case Details
Subject: {!$Input:Case.Subject}
Description: {!$Input:Case.Description}
Status: {!$Input:Case.Status}
Priority: {!$Input:Case.Priority}
Type: {!$Input:Case.Type}
Origin: {!$Input:Case.Origin}

## Recent Inbound Emails (last 10, newest first)
{!$Input:emailsJson}

## SLA Milestone Status
{!$Input:milestonesJson}

## Instructions
1. Analyse the case details, email content and tone, and SLA milestone compliance.
2. Identify specific escalation risk signals (e.g. unanswered emails, violated milestones, hostile language, repeated contacts, churn indicators).
3. Assign an escalation_risk_score as an integer from 0 (no risk) to 100 (imminent escalation/churn).
4. Assign an escalation_risk_level using ONLY one of these exact values: Low, Medium, High, Critical.
5. Summarise the detected signals in escalation_risk_signals (one or two sentences).
6. Provide a concrete escalation_recommended_action for the service agent to take.

## Scoring guidance
- 0 to 25: Low - routine case, no concerning signals
- 26 to 50: Medium - some friction or SLA risk, monitor closely
- 51 to 75: High - clear escalation signals, proactive intervention needed
- 76 to 100: Critical - imminent escalation, churn risk, immediate action required

## Required Output Format - return this JSON object and nothing else
{"escalation_risk_score": 0, "escalation_risk_level": "Low", "escalation_risk_signals": "summary of detected signals", "escalation_recommended_action": "specific action for the agent"}
